# Output Format

Produce a **Features Request** document:

```markdown
# Features Request

## Feature: [EXISTING-F001] <name>
### Description
<detailed description of what this feature does>
### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] <criterion 1: specific and testable>
- [ ] <criterion 2>
### Dependencies
- <dependency on other features, e.g., [EXISTING-F002]>
### Priority
<high/medium/low>
```

**Rules:**
- Use `[EXISTING-F001]`, `[EXISTING-F002]`, etc. — the EXISTING- prefix marks these as features extracted from existing code, not new requirements
- Derive acceptance criteria from what the code actually does (not aspirational)
- Every acceptance criterion must be specific and testable
- Group related functionality into single features (e.g., "User Authentication" not "Login" + "Logout" + "Register" separately)
- Dependencies must reference feature IDs
